# Cloudflare Pages _redirects. Copied verbatim from `frontend/public/` into
# `dist/` at build time by Vite's static-asset pass.
#
# Goal: GSC reports "page avec redirection" because the canonical sitemap
# URL `/grille` 308-redirects to `/grille/`. We want the bare path to be
# the served URL.
#
# Pages' default "auto trailing slash" canonicalizer runs BEFORE the
# `_redirects` table is consulted (verified via preview deploy 2026-05-18:
# explicit `/grille/ → /grille 308` rules never fired). The only way to
# claim the bare path is a `200` rewrite — that serves the destination's
# content under the requested URL, bypassing the canonicalizer entirely.
#
# Format: `<source>  <destination>  <status>`. 200 = rewrite (serve dest
# content, keep requested URL). 308 = permanent redirect, preserves method.
# First match wins.

# Bare-path rewrites — Pages serves `<slug>.html` content on `/<slug>`.
/grille              /grille.html              200
/grilles             /grilles.html             200
/aide                /aide.html                200
/mentions-legales    /mentions-legales.html    200
/confidentialite     /confidentialite.html     200
/privacy             /privacy.html             200

# Trailing-slash collapse for any legacy inbound link. These fire AFTER
# Pages' canonicalizer because the bare path is already claimed above
# (so the canonicalizer has nothing left to redirect FROM).
/grille/             /grille                    308
/grilles/            /grilles                   308
/aide/               /aide                      308
/mentions-legales/   /mentions-legales          308
/confidentialite/    /confidentialite           308
/privacy/            /privacy                   308
/compte/             /compte                    308
